<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-342] Typo in section 14.8.6 Returning a Deactivated OST to Service</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-342</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Under the section where you reactivate an ost on the client side it looks lie there is a typo...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the entry given is as follows:&lt;br/&gt;
client# lctl set_param osc.fsname-OSTnumber-*.active=0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which is the same entry from 14.8.3 where you deactivate the ost on the client side:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lctl set_param osc.fsname-OSTnumber-*.active=0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t it be active=1 to reactivate?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
